## Testing Checklist

Run `~/dev/ClockEvent/dtest.sh` to deploy, then:

- [ ] Verify clock still displays correctly (time + date)
- [ ] Right-click > Configure opens settings dialog
- [ ] Calendars tab: "Add Calendar" button works, can type label and paste iCal URL
- [ ] Calendars tab: enable/disable checkbox works, delete button works
- [ ] Calendars tab: hit Apply, verify events load (check logs/test.log for "Loaded X events")
- [ ] Appearance tab: 12h/24h toggle works, days ahead spinner works
- [ ] General tab: refresh interval spinner works
- [ ] Events display with month headers (e.g., "March 2026")
- [ ] Date badges show on left (day-of-week + day number), grouped for same-date events
- [ ] Event blocks show title (bold) + time range
- [ ] All-day events show "All day" instead of time range
- [ ] Scrolling works when many events are loaded
- [ ] Clicking an event opens Google Calendar day view in browser
- [ ] Clicking [+] button opens Google Calendar new event page in browser
